data.content:
**In .NET 11, all synchronous I/O on the EF Core Cosmos DB provider is fully removed — no opt-in exists anymore.** Your `.NET 10` sync-over-async workaround no longer works.

Every call in your repository will **throw at runtime**:
- `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()` → always throw
- `SaveChanges()` → always throws

**Fix:** Convert to async throughout:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
        => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
        => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
        => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to update all callers to `await` the new async methods. There is no workaround — the Cosmos SDK is async-only, and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it.

**Tracking issue:** [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059)
